I don't know, bro. Are you happy with your life? And if you aren't, what would no longer looking at this stuff change? A thing I've found is that stopping shit isn't going to magically fix your issues. It just means you no longer do a thing. With things that are unhealthy, there's obviously a rather direct positive effect. Stop eating as much, and you lose weight. Stop smoking, and you will be healthier. But say you picked up those habits as a response to stress in your life, it will not take away the stress and you will have to deal with it. It might give you a kick in the ass to deal with that stress because you're no longer engaging in your preferred coping strategy, but dealing with that stress is still the ticket and nixing your coping strategy doesn't automatically do that.

So really, the only one who can answer that question is you.
